member.summary:
Data about type`s relationships.
Note:
In order to include relationships you should set SchemaProfile's IncludeProperties to true.
In order to filter relationships you should use RelationshipProfile.
For example:
1) getSchemaService().getServiceContext().setProfile( new RelationshipProfile(null, RelationshipNameFilter.SPECIFIED, "relation name to return", TargetRoleFilter.SPECIFIED, "child", null, -1));
TypeInfo typeInfo = getSchemaService().getTypeInfo(getEnv().getDefaultDocbaseName(), "default", "dm_document", null);
That means that only relationships with name "relation name to return" and which have the given type (dm_document in this example) as a `child` will be returned by the SchemaService.
2)getSchemaService().getServiceContext().setProfile( new RelationshipProfile(null, null, null, TargetRoleFilter.SPECIFIED, "parent", null, -1));
TypeInfo typeInfo = getSchemaService().getTypeInfo(getEnv().getDefaultDocbaseName(), "default", "dm_document", null);
That means that only relationships which have the given type as a `parent` will be returned by the SchemaService.
